primary_outcome.description:
The therapeutic failure is defined as any of following cases:
CDAI > 220 with at least 70-point increase from baseline over two consecutive visits 12 weeks apart or CDAI > 300 at any time point during the study;
need of any change in therapy for CD except the ones planned per protocol in each group of the study;
need of surgery related to CD or of stricture endoscopic dilatation.
